{# ── case-references.njk ──
   design-backlog idea #22 ("tier-aware reference count callout"): renders
   the References chapter straight from mvp-references.json at build time,
   replacing 31 hand-duplicated copies of the same per-tone link lists that
   used to be baked directly into each case's own index.njk. Same "two
   independent copies can silently drift" bug class this backlog has fixed
   elsewhere (readMin, flagship, principle) — here caught before it ever
   drifted (a full diff of all 31 cases found 0 mismatches against this
   file), but the fix removes the possibility going forward rather than
   leaving the duplication in place.

   The per-tone count is real by construction: it's just that tone's array
   length from the same data the list below it is rendered from, so it
   can never say a number the list doesn't back up. #}
{% set refs = mvpReferences[slug] %}
{% if refs %}
<section class="case-chapter case-references" data-chapter="references">
  <h3>References</h3>
  {% for tone in ["junior", "mid", "staff"] %}
    {% if refs[tone] and refs[tone].length %}
    <div class="tone-{{ tone }}">
      <p class="case-references__count">{{ refs[tone].length }} reference{{ 's' if refs[tone].length != 1 else '' }} at this level</p>
      <ol>
        {% for link in refs[tone] %}
          <li>{{ link | safe }}</li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ol>
    </div>
    {% endif %}
  {% endfor %}
</section>
{% endif %}
